description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Title – Configuration Analyst&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Base – Edward Jenner Court, Brockworth&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Salary –£31,365 to £37,890 per annum (Band 6)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hours per week – 37.5&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;1 x Fixed Term contract/secondment opportunity for up to 12 months&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;*Internal applicants who wish to be considered for a secondment opportunity should discuss with their line manager the suitability of a possible secondment.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Are you educated to degree level or have equivalent experience with excellent IT skills, basic SQL knowledge, a willingness to learn advanced SQL skills &amp; undertake a testing qualification?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Are you interested in Clinical Systems, with the chance to develop new skills and knowledge to influence this key aspect of modern healthcare?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen to join our dynamic and supportive Clinical Systems Team initially on a fixed term basis, but with potential to become a permanent position.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Clinical Systems Team is responsible for the overall development, delivery and management of the Trusts Clinical Systems RiO, SystmOne, IAPTus, Lilie and SoelHealth.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Configuration Analysts are principally involved in system change, mapping out processes, specifically configuring system developments to meet all requirements, testing and deployment. There are opportunities to contribute to a variety of projects working with different systems &amp; people across the Trust from a variety of services and teams.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We are looking for a confident person who is enthusiastic about the benefits of electronic patient records. Excellent communication and problem-solving skills are essential, as the post-holder is required to work with clinicians, administrative support staff and managers at all levels.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Being a proactive quick learner with excellent attention to detail are essential skills required to gain sound knowledge and expertise in the front and back ends of our Clinical Systems.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This role also provides support to the wider Clinical Systems Team, so being a team player with the ability to multi-task and prioritise work is essential.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The post-holder will need to work flexibly between the hours of 8am and 5.30pm with occasional weekend and evening working. We are an enthusiastic, dynamic team whose members actively supportive each other.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;If you have a keen interest in Clinical Systems and would enjoy working as part of a team in a busy and varied role, we would welcome your application.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For further details on this vacancy please contact Laura Collins-Mills,Clinical Systems Change and Development Manager, on07827 880052or Ben Land, Clinical Analyst, on07776 160969.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The qualification, training &amp; experience requirements for the role are underlined in the Job Description/Person Specification.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Trust aims to recruit and retain the best possible staff who, through the application of their skills, qualification and experience, will make a positive contribution to our business of providing quality health care services. It is the Trust’s view that the costs associated with moving house in order to take up a post with us should not restrict our ability to recruit the excellent people we need, therefore we support staff to relocate with our relocation policy.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post requires the post holder to be able to undertake all statutory and mandatory training and post holders must be able to undertake physical interventions. Fitness for physical intervention will be assessed by Occupational Health.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To ensure you fully understand how the Trust, as a Data Controller, will process and store your data please read the attached document ‘ Applicant and Staff Privacy Notice’ prior to applying for the role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Candidates for any staff appointment shall, when making application, disclose in writing to the Trust whether they are related to any governor. Failure to disclose such a relationship may disqualify a candidate and, if appointed, may render him/her liable to dismissal.&lt;/p&gt;
